### Step 3: Verify README structure

The README at `sdk/azurestackhci/Azure.ResourceManager.Hci/README.md` currently contains all required sections but these need attention:

| Section | Status | Action |
|---|---|---|
| Getting started → Install | ✅ Present | No change |
| Getting started → Prerequisites | ✅ Present | No change |
| Getting started → Authenticate | ✅ Present | No change |
| Key concepts | ⚠️ Thin — only links to general docs | Add 2–3 sentences about HCI-specific concepts (cluster, arc settings, edge devices) |
| Examples | ⚠️ Missing new resource types | Add subsections per Step 2 above |
| Troubleshooting | ✅ Present | No change |
| Next steps | ✅ Present | No change |
| Contributing | ✅ Present | No change |

Use `sdk/keyvault/Azure.Security.KeyVault.Secrets/README.md` as the canonical reference for section formatting and tone.

### Step 4: Validate

Run these commands in order. Each must succeed before proceeding to the next.

1. `dotnet build sdk/azurestackhci/Azure.ResourceManager.Hci/`
2. `dotnet test sdk/azurestackhci/Azure.ResourceManager.Hci/ --filter TestCategory!=Live`
3. `eng/scripts/Update-Snippets.ps1 azurestackhci` — injects snippet code into README placeholders; check `git diff` afterwards to confirm README was updated
4. `eng/scripts/Export-API.ps1 azurestackhci` — no public API surface change is expected, but run to confirm
5. `dotnet format sdk/azurestackhci/Azure.ResourceManager.Hci/`

</details>

